label.value: Powder for Rectal Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a rectal solution.

label.value: Powder for Rectal Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain a rectal suspension.
Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powder intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a sealant.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Fish Treatment Dosage Form

value.value: Powder to be used to produce a solution intended for the treatment of fish by immersion.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified aqueous liquid to obtain a solution for infusion.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Injection/Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for injection/infusion.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Injection/Skin-Prick Test Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for injection/skin-prick test.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Intraocular Irrigation Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for intraocular irrigation.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Iontophoresis Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for iontophoresis.

label.value: Powder for Solution for Skin-Prick Test Dosage Form

value.value: Solid sterile preparation consisting of one or more powder intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain a solution for skin-prick test.

label.value: Powder for Suspension for Fish Treatment Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation for veterinary use consisting of one or more powders intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain a suspension for fish treatment by immersion.

Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders that may include excipients to facilitate dissolution in water and to obtain the characteristics of a syrup, intended to be dissolved in water to obtain a syrup.

label.value: Powder for Use in Drinking Water Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation for veterinary use consisting of one or more powder intended to be dissolved in the animal drinking water.

label.value: Powder for Use in Drinking Water/Milk Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation for veterinary use consisting of one or more powders intended to be dissolved in the animal drinking water, milk or milk replacer.

label.value: Powder, Dispersion and Solvent for Concentrate for Dispersion for Infusion Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder and sterile dispersion, both of which contain active substance(s), and sterile solvent intended for the preparation of a concentrate for dispersion for infusion; it is prepared as specified in the packaging information; the resulting concentrate for dispersion for infusion must subsequently be diluted before administration as a dispersion for infusion.

label.value: Powder, Solvent and Matrix for Implantation Matrix Dosage Form

value.value: Sterile powder (including freeze-dried powder), sterile solvent and sterile matrix intended for the preparation of an implantation matrix, for example by dissolving the powder in the solvent and using the resulting solution to impregnate the matrix. The powder contains active ingredient(s); the matrix does not contain active ingredient(s).
Pre-filled tube for the administration of a medicinal product to the gastroenteral tract.
Filled container, usually fitted with an injection needle, containing a sterile, single-dose parenteral preparation.

Filled container for administering a liquid or semi-solid pharmaceutical form to the oral cavity, containing the final preparation in one compartment, or the components necessary for its preparation in different compartments.

Filled container for administering a liquid or semi-solid pharmaceutical form to the oral cavity, containing the final preparation in one compartment, or the components necessary for its preparation in different compartments.
A type of specialized pharmaceutical dose form that is used in the preparation of products such as medicated feeding stuffs.

label.value: Premix for Medicated Feeding Stuff Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid, semi-solid or solid preparation intended to facilitate oral administration of active substances to animals. Premixes for medicated feeding stuff are used exclusively in the preparation of medicated feeding stuffs. Used as powders or granules, they are free-flowing and homogeneous. Used in liquid form, they are homogeneous suspensions or solutions which may be obtained from thixotropic gels or structured liquids. The particle size and other properties are such as to ensure uniform distribution of the active substance(s) in the final feeding stuff.

Container suited for compressed, liquefied or dissolved gas fitted with a device to enable, after its actuation, a controlled spontaneous release of the contents at atmospheric pressure and room temperature.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for inhalation use. The preparation is presented in a pressurized container fitted with a metering dose valve.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for inhalation use. The preparation is presented in a pressurized container usually fitted with a metering dose valve.
Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for inhalation use. The preparation is presented in a pressurized container fitted with a metering dose valve.
Device for prick testing of allergen products.
Release of the substance(s) over a longer duration than would be achieved with a conventional-release product, achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method.

Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a hard shell containing a solid or semi-solid formulation, showing a slower release of the active substance(s) than that of a conventional-release capsule. Prolonged release is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method. Hard prolonged-release capsules are intended for oral use.

Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a soft shell containing a semi-solid or liquid formulation, showing a slower release of the active substance(s) than that of a conventional-release capsule. Prolonged release is achieved by a special formulation design and/or manufacturing method. Soft prolonged-release capsules are intended for oral use.

label.value: Extended Release Granule for Oral Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of prolonged-release granules intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an oral suspension.

label.value: Prolonged-Release Granules for Oral Suspension in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of prolonged-release granules for oral suspension presented in a sachet.

label.value: Prolonged-Release Granules in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of prolonged-release granules presented in a sachet.

label.value: Prolonged-Release Solution for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a solution intended for administration by injection; the active substance(s) are released over an extended period of time.

label.value: Prolonged-Release Suspension for Injection Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid sterile preparation consisting of a suspension intended for administration by injection; the active substance(s) are released over an extended period of time.

label.value: Prolonged-Release Suspension for Injection in Pre-filled Syringe Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of a prolonged-release suspension for injection presented in a pre-filled syringe.

label.value: Pulsatile Release Intraruminal Device Dosage Form

value.value: Solid single-dose preparation intended for oral use in ruminant animals. It is designed to be retained in the rumen to deliver the active substance(s) in a pulsatile manner by the release of a specific quantity of active substance(s) at one or several defined intermediate intervals. This may be achieved by corrosion by ruminal fluids of the metallic elements of the intraruminal device which leads to sequential release of the constituent units which are usually in the form of tablets.
A radionuclide produced for the radio-labelling of another substance prior to administration.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution containing a radionuclide produced for the radio-labelling of another substance prior to administration.
Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a soft capsule of elongated shape suitable for rectal use, containing a liquid or semi-solid formulation, and which may have a lubricating coating.

Liquid preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for rectal use or for diagnostic purposes. Rectal emulsions are usually presented in containers with a volume in the range of 2.5 mL to 2000 mL. The container is fitted with an applicator or an applicator is provided separately.

Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for rectal use or for diagnostic purposes. Rectal solutions are usually presented in containers with a volume in the range of 2.5 mL to 2000 mL. The container is fitted with an applicator or an applicator is provided separately.

Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for rectal use or for diagnostic purposes. Rectal suspension are usually presented in containers with a volume in the range of 2.5 mL to 2000 mL. The container is fitted with an applicator or an applicator is provided separately.
Solid single-dose preparation consisting of a suitable material impregnated with active substance(s) intended to be inserted in the rectum for a limited period of time usually for a local effect.

The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by bringing it into contact with the affected area for a short period of time, e.g. by pouring it over the area and allowing it to drain away, or swilling it around the area and then removing it.
A container, usually a bottle, fitted with a roll-on applicator
